50|$|An <b>alcohol</b> <b>interlock</b> {{consists}} basically of {{an instrument}} measuring breath alcohol and a vehicle immobilizer. The installation {{is possible in}} different types of vehicles like passenger cars, buses, transporters, motorcycles or trains. A breath sample has to be delivered to the <b>alcohol</b> <b>interlock</b> before the vehicle motor can be started or the vehicle can be moved. The <b>alcohol</b> <b>interlock</b> will prevent the driver to start the motor if he/she has an alcohol concentration above a predetermined limit value.|$|E
